// Initialize the static member variable
std::vector<std::function<void(std::string)>> DeepLinkAdapter::_listeners;

// Rest of the code...
void DeepLinkAdapter::addListener(std::function<void(std::string)> listener) {
    _listeners.push_back(listener);
}
```

By providing the definition `std::vector<std::function<void(std::string)>> DeepLinkAdapter::_listeners;` outside the class body in the implementation file (e.g., DeepLinkAdapter.cpp), you ensure that the `_listeners` static member variable is properly defined and linked with the rest of the code.

Make sure that the definition is present in only one translation unit (source file) and that you're linking all the necessary object files together during compilation.

By correctly defining the static member variable outside the class, the "unresolved external symbol" error should be resolved.

